<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Design on Josh Giles</title><link>https://joshlgiles.com/categories/design/</link><description>Recent content in Design on Josh Giles</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 03 May 2023 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://joshlgiles.com/categories/design/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Create editable grids in Power Pages without using code</title><link>https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/</link><pubDate>Wed, 03 May 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/Software.jpg" alt="Featured image of post Create editable grids in Power Pages without using code" />&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Power Pages is a helpful tool that makes it easy to create websites using low-code development. It also allows for rich integration with other Power Platform solutions.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Recently, I had a requirement to use editable grids within Power Pages for list data. I managed to find some documentation on using code components for Power Pages here: &lt;a class="link" href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/power-pages/configure/tutorial-pcf-code" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/power-pages/configure/tutorial-pcf-code&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Reading this, I found it confusing to understand as I felt it lacked clarity on whether you could in fact use editable grids.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>To help streamline the process and save you time, I have put together a quick guide on how to use an editable grid in your Power Pages lists.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="add-the-editable-grid-component-to-your-desired-table">Add the Editable Grid component to your desired table&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>I am using the Accounts table with a solution called &amp;ldquo;Test solution&amp;rdquo; for this demonstration.&lt;/p>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>Within your solution, navigate to Tables and then the ellipses and click &amp;ldquo;Switch to Classic&amp;rdquo;.
&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/NavigateToClassic.png"
width="1309"
height="572"
srcset="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/NavigateToClassic_hu1537ccfc154944d9a383562401d4955a_32585_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/NavigateToClassic_hu1537ccfc154944d9a383562401d4955a_32585_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Navigate to Classic Solutions"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="228"
data-flex-basis="549px"
>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Double click the Account Table (also called Entity).
&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/DoubleClickAccount.png"
width="1496"
height="889"
srcset="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/DoubleClickAccount_hubd371c81528a2a80c1d1084f798de9ea_92948_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/DoubleClickAccount_hubd371c81528a2a80c1d1084f798de9ea_92948_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Double Click Account"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="168"
data-flex-basis="403px"
>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Click the Controls tab and then Add Control&amp;hellip;
&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/ClickControl.png"
width="1546"
height="947"
srcset="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/ClickControl_hu0dca1054fed9d67ba2ff13a745888d33_123744_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/ClickControl_hu0dca1054fed9d67ba2ff13a745888d33_123744_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Click Control Tab"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="163"
data-flex-basis="391px"
>
&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/AddControl.png"
width="1842"
height="901"
srcset="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/AddControl_hu59a4223b167c9552b1e8f1bc0012108e_84405_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/AddControl_hu59a4223b167c9552b1e8f1bc0012108e_84405_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Add Control"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="204"
data-flex-basis="490px"
>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>In the Add control menu, search for and select the PowerApps grid control, then click Add.
&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/ClickAdd.png"
width="515"
height="471"
srcset="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/ClickAdd_hu6f14a01637a75e92dde284a5087de878_16049_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/ClickAdd_hu6f14a01637a75e92dde284a5087de878_16049_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Click Add"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="109"
data-flex-basis="262px"
>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Ensure that the Power Apps grid control is enabled for Web and Phone/Tablet if required.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Select the control to bring up the properties.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Set the value of Enable editing to &amp;ldquo;Yes&amp;rdquo;. You can enable other properties too if required, and I recommend you check out the documentation to find out which each property does.
&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/EnableEditing.png"
width="1828"
height="867"
srcset="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/EnableEditing_hu79801a84ac7854df43a3b861f186e7b8_90850_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/EnableEditing_hu79801a84ac7854df43a3b861f186e7b8_90850_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Enable editing"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="210"
data-flex-basis="506px"
>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Click Save, and then click Publish
&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/SavePublish.png"
width="1828"
height="867"
srcset="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/SavePublish_huc0d6e8170324ea9415e1765e0c5b10d3_90735_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/SavePublish_huc0d6e8170324ea9415e1765e0c5b10d3_90735_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Save and Publish"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="210"
data-flex-basis="506px"
>&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;h2 id="add-the-component-to-portal-management">Add the component to Portal Management&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Now we have our editable grid added to our table, we need to configure Power Pages to use it. The first step is to add a new List so it can then be selected when adding it to our page.&lt;/p>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>Navigate to make.powerpages.microsoft.com&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Select the elipses against your site and select Portal management
&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/PortalManagement2-min.png"
width="1837"
height="886"
srcset="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/PortalManagement2-min_hueda281a952a99c9df761f8dacd473054_131159_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/PortalManagement2-min_hueda281a952a99c9df761f8dacd473054_131159_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Portal Edit"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="207"
data-flex-basis="497px"
>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Under Content, go to Lists, click New
&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/NewList.png"
width="1827"
height="895"
srcset="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/NewList_hu2dbb3243884683df0e253ef8bc11b3a6_86039_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/NewList_hu2dbb3243884683df0e253ef8bc11b3a6_86039_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Add new list"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="204"
data-flex-basis="489px"
>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Give your List a Name, select the Table, and the website
&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/NameTableWebsite.png"
width="1844"
height="920"
srcset="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/NameTableWebsite_hu7b3afd26e933cb32cafab4423a3ae13d_75199_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/NameTableWebsite_hu7b3afd26e933cb32cafab4423a3ae13d_75199_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="List name and Table selection"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="200"
data-flex-basis="481px"
>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Add your views
&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/AddViews.png"
width="1827"
height="937"
srcset="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/AddViews_hua252c30f51692c73c1676e79a62b74d5_69213_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/AddViews_hua252c30f51692c73c1676e79a62b74d5_69213_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Add views"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="194"
data-flex-basis="467px"
>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Make sure that Use a configured code component is set to yes. You can change other properties here as needed, and then click Save and Close
&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/CodeComponentYes.png"
width="1802"
height="908"
srcset="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/CodeComponentYes_hudc9a76f4751bac938aeb24c7b1e72da6_68659_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/CodeComponentYes_hudc9a76f4751bac938aeb24c7b1e72da6_68659_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Set Code component to Yes"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="198"
data-flex-basis="476px"
>&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;h2 id="add-the-editable-grid-to-your-page">Add the editable grid to your page&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>The final step is to add the list to our page and test it out.&lt;/p>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>navigate back to your Power Page site and edit it
&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/EditPage.png"
width="1834"
height="858"
srcset="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/EditPage_hu9c287c03f313ba0d7b529c8c4bbf7a47_462443_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/EditPage_hu9c287c03f313ba0d7b529c8c4bbf7a47_462443_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Edit Page"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="213"
data-flex-basis="513px"
>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>go to the page where you wish to add the editable grid. In my example I have a test page called Temp
&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/GoToTemp.png"
width="1821"
height="893"
srcset="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/GoToTemp_hu248de8d61ecf720d9a8d8fe173eae28e_88261_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/GoToTemp_hu248de8d61ecf720d9a8d8fe173eae28e_88261_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Navigate to page"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="203"
data-flex-basis="489px"
>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Add a List to the page under the Choose a component to add to this section
&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/AddList.png"
width="1821"
height="893"
srcset="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/AddList_hu186975755e21ed13d1f9e5ec28ebdbab_88764_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/AddList_hu186975755e21ed13d1f9e5ec28ebdbab_88764_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Add a List"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="203"
data-flex-basis="489px"
>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Select the existing list we added in the previous steps, in my case it&amp;rsquo;s the Test view with Grid
&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/AddtestViewWithGrid.png"
width="714"
height="501"
srcset="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/AddtestViewWithGrid_hu13d2a2ff88ab0c830d404a386bccd3a2_30466_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/AddtestViewWithGrid_hu13d2a2ff88ab0c830d404a386bccd3a2_30466_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Add list from menu"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="142"
data-flex-basis="342px"
>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Sync and preview your page, you should now see the editable grid displayed in the preview page.
&lt;img src="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/SyncPreview.png"
width="1843"
height="907"
srcset="https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/SyncPreview_hu7adb306060f996adc980a4619b84d06d_84703_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://joshlgiles.com/p/create-out-of-the-box-editable-grids-in-powerpages/SyncPreview_hu7adb306060f996adc980a4619b84d06d_84703_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Sync and Save"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="203"
data-flex-basis="487px"
>&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
